The Zondo Commission will hear Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) related evidence from the Head of the Legal Division at PRASA, Martha Ngoye and PRASA employee, Tiro Holele. The Commission will also hear Transnet related evidence from former Transnet Chief Financial Officer, Gary Pita. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry will hear Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (Prasa) related evidence on Tuesday afternoon. The commission will hear evidence from the Head of the Legal Division at Prasa, Martha Ngoye and Prasa employee, Tiro Holele. WATCH: Gigaba continues state capture inquiry testimony Later, the commission will also hear Transnet-related evidence from former Transnet Chief Financial Officer, Gary Pita.